French PM Bayrou turns to confidence vote to defuse 2026 budget defeat
description: François Bayrou has called for a vote of confidence in his government on September 8 in the Assemblée Nationale, saying he seeks 'clarification.' But his fall seems all but certain, as both the left and the far right have already announced they will vote against him.

Poland's new president vetoes bill extending aid to Ukrainian refugees
description: Karol Nawrocki has refused to sign into law a bill that would extend aid to Ukrainian refugees without work requirements. This veto illustrates the power struggle that the new head of state is determined to wage against the pro-European government.

headline: Libyan coast guards fire on Ocean Viking in international waters
description: The humanitarian vessel operated by the NGO SOS Méditerranée came under automatic gunfire from two masked Libyan coast guards for about 20 minutes on Sunday, August 24.

headline: Trump steps up campaign against renewable energy, orders halt to offshore wind farm construction
description: The US administration is stopping construction on a nearly completed offshore wind farm, operated by the Danish group Orsted, off the northeast coast of the United States.

headline: Jacques Rancière, philosopher: 'Today, the people fueled by resentment manufactured by billionaires dominate the public sphere'
description: 'May '68 Thinkers Reflect On Trump Era' (1/6). The philosopher of emancipation examines the roots of the current reactionary offensive. He views contemporary utopian micro-communities as new ways of 'living as equals.'

description: Taras Fedorenko, a 25-year-old Ukrainian photographer and videographer based in Kyiv, shares with Le Monde the story of a generation striving for a 'normal' life amid the ongoing conflict with Russia.

headline: Life in the West Bank settlement of Kedem Arava: 'We're not taking anyone's place, there is only sand around us'
description: Established in 2017 near the Jordanian border, the Kedem Arava settlement contains prefabricated homes housing some 60 families, former city dwellers seeking a life closer to nature. While most residents deny ideological motivation, their presence fully aligns with the annexation of Palestinian territory sought by the Israeli far right.

headline: Contested Sicily-Calabria bridge embodies contradictions of Giorgia Meloni's Italy
description: A government project to build a road and rail bridge linking Sicily to Calabria on mainland Italy has sparked concerns, hopes, desires and heated protests.
